                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote type="illustration"> Two double page miniatures at the
                                beginning (<locus from="1b" to="1b">1b</locus> and <locus from="2a"
                                    to="2a">2a</locus>) and end (<locus from="270b" to="270b"
                                    >270b</locus> and <locus from="271a" to="271a">271a</locus>),
                                both enclosed in richly illuminated borders. </decoNote>
                            <decoNote type="decoration">Illuminated headings
                                with richly decorated margins on folios <locus from="2b" to="2b"
                                    >2b</locus> (Preface), <locus from="66b" to="66b">66b</locus>
                                (Qasidas), <locus from="131b" to="131b">131b</locus> (Short Poems),
                                    <locus from="141b" to="141b">141b</locus> (Ghazals) and <locus
                                    from="253b" to="253b">253b</locus> (Quatrains).</decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <decoNote>Modern red leather slip-case. Contemporary binding very
                                similar to that of Persian MS 35 (the gilt panels on the outer faces
                                are from the same die) and no doubt from the same workshop, with
                                panels of inscription of cut-out and inlaid coloured leather and
                                cut-out work on the doublures.</decoNote>
                        </bindingDesc>
